title: Cloudy with light rain on Wednesday — Pagasa

organizations.name: philippine atmospheric, geophysical and astronomical services administration

text:
By: Frances Mangosing - Reporter / @FMangosingINQ INQUIRER.net / 07:22 AM January 25, 2017 Clouds can be seen over Mindanao in this satellite photo released by Pagasa on Wednesday morning. PAGASA PHOTO 
Parts of the country will experience rain due to the tail-end of a cold front in the eastern part of Mindanao and the northeast monsoon in Luzon and Visayas, the state weather bureau said on Wednesday. 
Mindanao will have cloudy skies with light to moderate rain and thunderstorms, the Philippine Atmospheric, Geophysical and Astronomical Services Administration (Pagasa) said. 
Cloudy skies with light rain is expected over Luzon and Eastern and Central Visayas becoming moderate to occasionally heavy rain over the provinces of Aurora and Quezon, it added. ADVERTISEMENT 
The rest of the Visayas will have partly cloudy to cloudy skies with isolated light rain. 
Moderate to strong winds blowing from the northeast will prevail over the entire archipelago with moderate to rough seas, Pagasa also said. CBB
